Tuesday marks the first anniversary since the passing of struggle icon Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. South Africans have taken to social media with the hashtag WinnieMadikizelaMandela to pay tribute to Mama Winnie, who passed away in a Johannesburg hospital at the age of 81. Some have reiterated calls for the Cape Town International Airport to be renamed after Madikizela-Mandela. The South African State Theatre has also dedicated Tuesdayâ€™s performances to the memory of Mama Winnie. See related tweets below:      